runs.comm: tossed up outside off and he reaches out and pushes it towards mid-off
gives it a lot of air, loops towards middle and he drills it down the track and Doherty misfields, wild throw from mid-on
wide outside off and driven wide of cover but long-off comes across and mops up
tossed up outside off and driven down back to the bowler
Haffez gives him the charge for the loft but ends up mistiming it to micwicket
floated down the leg side and Nazir slips at the crease as he tries to sweep

you should have seen the swing! Starc comes over the wicket and gets it to swing back in sharply from the off stump line, Hafeez tried to flick it away but didn't read the movement, the umpire took his time, landed on off and replays showed that  crashing into middle and leg
lands it full to Jamshed and he drills it back to the bowler
was that a chance? Yes it was a drop by Maxwell at first slip, he dragged a full and wide delivery and the bat hit the pitch, the ball lobbed off the outside edge and Maxwell juggled and fumbled
tucked away across the line wide of midwicket for a couple
bangs it in short and he weaves away from the bouncer
drifts on the pads and he mistimes the flick to the leg side
gets away with the friendliest of full tosses, so wide outside off and Jamshed can only find cover
outside edge again off Jamshed's bat on the drive but on the bounce to first slip, did well to stop it with one hand though
gets across and mistimes the drive back to the bowler
full and wide and Watson gets away with it again, off the meat of the bat but can't beat the packed off-side field
that's five dot balls gentlemen, Jamshed gives room to whack it across the line but gets an inside edge to midwicket
the wait ends finally for Jamshed, after 5 dot balls he crashes a half volley wide outside off past mid-off and cover, super shot
really wide outside the off stump, surprised that wasn't called
drifts on the pads and he tucks it wide of square leg
flashy drive outside the off stump by Jamshed, no foot movement
full on the pads and he tucks it wide of midewicket
lands on middle and gets an inside edge to the pads, half-hearted appeal by Starc
gets across and punches it wide of mid-off, quiet start by Nazir's standards
loose delivery by Cummins, friendly half volley swinging in on the pads and he whips it away wide of short fine leg
drifts towards the pads again and he clips it wide of short fine leg but the sweeper cuts it off
hits the deck too hard and Nazir ducks under the bouncer, the bowler is penalised
shot of authority! Good length outside the off stump and a touch wide, Nazir uses the crease and crashes it wide of cover
tries to force it away but mistimes it to the on side
stays back and mistimes it to mid-on
slightly full and Nazir's attempt at a straight drive finds mid-on, played a bit too early
Jamshed gives the charge and tries to hammer it away but cannot beat mid-on, seeing quite a few drives find the fielders today
middle and leg line and he rocks backwards and clips it wide of square leg
slower ball and Nazir waits for it and drives to cover, tells Jamshed to stay back

Watson gets away with another full toss! Hardly a wicket-taking delivery but everything's going his way, Nazir meets it outside the leg stump and the ball hit the bottom half of the bat and spooned tamely to mid-off, easiest of catches, Nazir wouldn't want to see a replay of that, Nazir should have hit it straighter
keeps a touch low and he gets off the mark with a clip to square leg
pushes it down to long-on for a single
tossed up on middle and clipped to square leg
comes round the wicket, lands it short and wide outside off and thumps it to sweeper cover
works it against the turn down to long-on
flatter on the pads and he clips it down to deep midwicket
pushes it wide of cover for a single
flatter delivery and skids through and he tucks it with the turn to deep square leg
tossed up on middle and tucked away wide of midwicket, no real turn
another full toss fails to get dispatched, Jamshed held back and gently worked it to deep midwicket
forceful reverse sweep and he places it to the sweeper on the off side
turns and grips and he gets an outside edge
pushes it down to mid-off
flicks it down to long-on for a single, another quiet over
tucks it away behind square on the on side for a single
fired down the leg side and he gets on his knee early and sweeps to fine leg
sweeps again and it's squarer on the on side
works it to the deep on the off side
gives himself room and thumps it on the back foot  wide of cover
flatter and quicker and he works it wide of long-on, Hussey's under pressure as they take 2
a boundary finally, tossed up outside off, lands on the half volley and he makes room and crashes it past the diving extra cover fielder
goes back and forces it away to the leg side
goes back at the crease and clips it wide of mid-on
fetches it from the off stump and sweeps
sloppy from Maxwell! Rare to see a fumble like this, Jamshed drives to mid-on and Maxwell was behind the ball and got a bad bounce, slipped through his legs - Sydney Harbour Bridge
turns and beats the outside edge and wade was so confident he charged forward with his appeal, the umpire wasn't convinced
cuts uppishly to deep backward point and Akmal ran the first hard but Jamshed was happy with one
starting to open up! Too short and it was the slower bouncer, read the length early and swiveled and pulled him high over square leg
slower ball outside off and he drives to sweeper cover
tries to squeeze it past backward point but can't beat the fielder
half volley outside off and he drives forcefully wide of cover and Hussey does well to slide and cut it off in front of the rope
slower ball and driven to the off side
Jamshed's got his eye in yeah! Tossed up on the off stump and he gets on his knee and slogs with the turn and comfortably clears deep midwicket
well bowled, fires it outside off on seeing the batsman charge, manages to dig it out
forces it away to the deep on the on side for a couple
chips it in the air and it lands well clear of mid-off and it's the fifty stand
makes a lot of room to bisect the gap square on the off side but he can't beat backward point
flatter and almost on a yorker length, he jams it back to the bowler
Jamshed's pressing the pedal here, welcomes Watson's new spell with a crisp lofted drive over the bowler's head and down to the sightscreen
goes for the slog and the ball clips his pad and rolls to the off side
makes room and swings across the line and mistimes it down to deep square leg
bowls it down the leg side and Akmal gets on his knee and sweeps to fine leg
full and wide outside off and Jamshed really had to drag his bat out to dig it out to the off side
full outside off and squirted out to cover
fetches that from outside off and sweeps him firmly in front of square to Hussey at deep midwicket
chips it over cover and the sweeper runs forward to stop it
spins into him and Akmal made room to cut against the turn and cramped himself for room, managed to place it to point
thump! Flatter and shorter and Jamshed rocks back and crashes it over the bowler's head
tossed up outside off and driven to long-on
sails away! Tossed up outside off and Akmal was on his knee and slogged cleanly over wide long-on, covered quite some distance
fired that really wide outside off and jamshed pulled out of the shot
sweeps in front of square and deep midwicket runs across and picks it up
flatter delivery and he drills it on the full wide of long-off
drills a full toss down the ground to long-off, should have put that away over the ropes
another full toss and he swung too early and got an outside edge to wade who couldn't take it, tough chance
holed out to long-on! Tossed up and he stayed at the crease and tried to loft him downtown, the ball dipped and landed safely in Warner's palms in front of the rope
drills it back to the bowler

Pakistan have lost their well set pair in a matter of three balls! Starc begins his new spell by bowling full from round the wicket, Kamran made room and tried to hammer it wide of extra cover but the fielder there, White, took a sharp catch falling to his right
fetches his first boundary already, short and angling in to him and he clubbed it over midwicket, comfortably clear of the fielders
crashes a full delivery wide of cover and picks up a couple to the sweeper
holds the length back and razzaq ducks under the bouncer
tries to pinch a quick single to cover but he's sent scampering back
slower ball and he hammers it straight to cover, takes a quick single
squeezes out a yorker straight to Watson at point, confusion in the running and Razzaq has to hurry back, Watson decides not to throw
swings too early at a slower ball and misses, Wade underarms the ball and it misses the stumps
slogged in the air just over midwicket's reach and it will be only a couple
makes room and he swishes at thin air
finally makes some solid contact, pitched up outside off and he makes room, gets under the bounce and lofts crisply over long-off
full outside off and drilled wide of long-off and did well to take the first one quickly
gives the charge and mistimes a full toss down to long-on
drags a full ball down to White at midwicket, cannot steal  a single there
Watson gets away with a length ball, Razzaq thumps it back to him, really Watson has gotten away with some ordinary balls today
full and wide outside off and Razzaq sizes up to hit it but withdraws the shot
top edge off the splice of the bat and it lands in the middle of nowhere in front of long-on
goes for the loft and it dips and lands well in front of long-on
Razzaq makes room and bashes a low full toss straight to extra cover
makes room and he drills a full ball straight towards mid-off, just a single
got the elevation he wanted, pitched up and Razzaq made room, got under the bounce and carved it over extra cover

short ball outside off and Razzaq made himself a lot of room to carve that over the off side, he was targeting the third man boundary but the ball swirled just behind backward point, Watson takes the catch behind the circle
a convincing edge, he makes room to a full delivery and shapes to drive straighter but gets an outside edge that bisects short third man and backward point
that's a good slower bouncer and Akmal swung hard and missed it completely
boom! Pitched up on the off stump and Afridi launches it crisply down the ground to long-off

that's as much as it gets with Afridi these days, Starc swung it in sharply from round the wicket, Afridi shuffled a long way across and exposed his stumps and his leg stump went back a couple of yards
low full toss and he clips it away to deep midwicket, not more than a single
another inswinging yorker on the leg stump and he swings and the ball only hits his pads and rolls away
almost a repeat of the previous dismissal, shuffled and exposed his stumps, tucked away behind square
slogs the final ball and mistimes it straight to midwicket, only a single and that will get them to 149
